cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.EC

This paper deals with the pricing strategies and regulatory policies for Internet Access Providers (APs) in the context of network congestion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves game theory and optimization techniques to derive optimal pricing schemes, which suggests the possibility of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) categories. The paper also discusses the impact of congestion on user experiences and providers' utility, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Finally, the paper discusses the social welfare implications of pricing strategies, which could be related to cs.EC (Economics and Computation) category.
